title: For Sale:  Polish Radom PPS-43 9mm Pistol (Welded Folder SMG, Semi-Auto) Used
postcontent:
Original Polish PPS-43C in a semi-auto version.  9mm caliber, considered a pistol due to overall length.  Welded Floder. Comes with 10 - 35rd mags.  

A very fun pistol that gets a lot of attention onn the range!

The PPS-43C (Pistolet-Pulemet Sudaeva, model of 1943 = Sudaev SMG) was born as an answer to the need for a weapon that is more compact and mobile than the PPSh-41, then in use by the Soviet Army.  The PPSh-41 was somewhat too long to be used by tank crews and mobile recon groups and paratroopers, so late in 1941, the Red Army issued a request for a new more compact sub machine gun (SMG).  The designer Sudaev initially designed his new SMG in 1942, and it was adopted under the designation of PPS-42.  The next year he refined the design, and this final model was designated as the PPS-43.  This model was manufactured in significant numbers (nearly two million PPS-43 weapons were manufactured between 1943 and 1946).  The PPS-43 is sometimes referred to as the best SMG of World War II. After WWII, it was widely exported to pro-Soviet regimes around the world, and widely copied.  This historical firearm has been re-designed to shoot from a closed bolt position.  The safety is located at the front of the trigger guard.  The receiver and barrel shroud are made from stamped steel.  The rear sight is an L-shaped flip type and is marked for 100 and 200 meters, the front sight is a fixed blade type.  The barrel is equipped with a simple muzzle brake.  This firearm is an ATF approved pistol.  The stock has no function and is permanently fixed in its folded position.

The bolt carrier is a chrome lined “enhanced AR-15” carrier with a properly staked gas key.  The “enhanced” means the lower part of the tail section is longer than a standard AR carrier but shorter than the M-16 carrier and is chrome lined.
The bolt is your standard AR bolt and is  MP (magnetic particle tested) 
The extractor features a black buffer and also an o-ring for more reliable extraction.

Barrel: CHF (cold hammer forged) from chrome moly vanadium and has a chrome lined bore and chamber with a 1:7 twist and are all individually HP (high pressure) tested (not batch tested).
Another feature of the M400 is an extractor support pin located inside the barrel extension.  This small pin supports the extractor in the event of a case failure or over pressurization and can prevent a complete blow out.
Additions: Magpul CTR buttstock ($100), Magpul enhanced trigger guard, Magpul MOE+ pistol grip, Samson back up iron sight (rear) ($120) Troy Charlie battle rail - full length quad rail. 
If the offer is right, ill include an AimPoint PRO red dot sight with 2 mounts, 3x's Magnifier made by Vortex Optics, a Troy vertical fore grip, a Fenix PD35 (850 Lumens max) with mount, and a Magpul MS-4 Tactical sling.
Conclusion: This AR has around 600 rounds through it and has not had one single failure. I am only looking to trade

You are bidding on a Colt Single Action Army Revolver in 32.20.
The Stamping on top of the Pistol is still crisp and legible.
The Stamping on the Barrel Reads COLT'S PT F.A. MFG. Co HARTFORD. CT. U.S.A.
On the left side of the Barrel is Stamped 32 W.C.F.
On the left side of the Frame is Stamped PAT SEPT. 19. 1871. The next line is Stamped JULY. 2. 72. JAN. 19. 75.
The Rampant Colt Stamp is still strong.
Only 8% of the Colt S.A.A. were manufactured in 32.20.
The Pistol was shipped to the Norvell Shapleigh Hardware Company on September 9, 1905.
See accompanying Colt Factory Archive Letter.
The Serial Number is 270XXX.
